Aside from self respect, ethical retardation, and lack of accomplishment issues, there are also very real quantifiable problems with people buying platinum/items for real cash. <br>
<br>
For starters, many of the e-bay suppliers are organized and can permacamp an area farming it 24/7 thereby depriving Joe Adventurer of the rewards of a given camp.  Seen stormfeather lately?  Unlike standard characters that play by the rules, cash farmers start out with the understanding that what they are doing is prohibited. There is no reason for them NOT to use third party software to detect rare/named spawns.  All they need to do is enter a zone, check their other box for spawns, and see what loot they have, then take their hydra in and it's all over.<br>
<br>
Second, they use exploits to gain platinum to sell. Remember the recent fletching nerf?  Thanks to pp traders that used a third party script to farm platinum, EVERY fletcher in the game was horribly affected. Now instead of making a few platinum on the way to 250 fletching, it costs nearly 50,000pp in total.<br>
<br>
Third, on the buyers side, Most e-bayed characters have no idea how to play their class. Sure they may have an uber level 65 manburning wizard, but they can easily get an entire raid wiped if they screw up and nuke at the wrong time. This goes for any class, it takes time to learn to play your character well.  Buying a character robs the buyer of critical knowledge that can only be gained through hundreds of hours of play. Grouping with an inept player will very possibly lead to a horrible death and a brutal CR.<br>
<br>
Fourth, by buying said items, you are encouraging scammers to use any method necessary to acquire goods, that includes outright stealing items (like horses), using the trade window macro . You are also opening yourself up to be scammed mercilously. Try complaining to SoE when someone doesn't deliver your uber sword of asskicking that you paid $100.00 for. I don't see your complaint getting much attention.<br>
<br>
Everyone is entitled to their opinion. But it's pretty clear to me that nothing positive can result from spending real cash on fictional items/platinum. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimjakkghostripper>Grimjakk Ghostripper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/02 1:24:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3323.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: one word</span><hr size=1> Traxxus... exactly right. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caillougna>Caillou GNA</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pebble with a bow</span><br>  Posts: 953<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/02 2:33:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3323.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: one word</span><hr size=1> As for a casual player thinking he/she is being shorted by, say, not having the plat to buy a horse.  Umm.... why do you think you are entitled to have a horse?  If you don't play a lot, why do you even need one?  if you play in the level range where a horse becomes more desirable, then you will also be in the level range where making money becomes more viable.  Simple.<br>
