 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caillougna>Caillou GNA</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pebble with a bow</span><br>  Posts: 954<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/02 3:59:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3323.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To stop some of it</span><hr size=1> I know the use/need for a horse, but a casual player who is hovering, say, in their 20s has -far- less need for a horse than a more frequent player in their 50s or 60s.  I play -a lot-, am now in my late 40s and I am starting to hit into the things that are making me money (well, combining incomes for Bippin and I... seems to be working *smirk*).  If I were to look at my -play- time vs a casual player's -play- time, we probably make about the same amount of plat though my -real- time (as in days, weeks, months by the real world calendar) would be less.  THAT is what I was saying.  It's true whether the object of desire is a horse, an uber stick of thwacking, a mighty sword of slicing and dicing, or whatever.  And, I still say there is no justification, in my mind, for the &quot;need&quot; to buy something in game with real world money.  <br>
<br>
I know when people say the server got blue... I still only think it is blue if we let it be... if we take the easy road and jsut drop it to OOC mechanics and pixels.  Bleah... I got bored of DII because it was nothing more than that.  The real purple of the server is in the hearts and creativity of those who roleplay and continue to do so. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naari@firionavie>Naari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/02 4:08:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3323.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To stop some of it</span><hr size=1> Remind me to stay clear of Noggy. Between this post and his post about too many guilds, it is clear he and I see things VERY differently.<br>
<br>
Others have stated reasons for why allowing people to buy plat, etc. with outside cash causes problems in game. I don't need to rehash that.<br>
<br>
I would like to deal with the whole gear issue.<br>
<br>
Yes horses are nice. Yes it would be great to have the most expensive one. Yes it would be great to even have the least expensive one. I don't. When I earn the money, I will.<br>
<br>
Is it necessary to have that or any other particular piece of gear? No.<br>
<br>
As I stated in the other thread, I could easily level my mage buck naked except for food, water, and pet components.<br>
<br>
In many situations I could level my cleric buck naked and my group wouldn't suffer for it. (Mana recovery rate is more important than Mana pool in many situations).<br>
<br>
If I was a melee type, gear would be more important. Even so, it isn't that difficult to cheaply equip a melee character with gear that would have been considered Uber when this game came out.<br>
<br>
What I am getting at is this - there is no need for a casual player to get items outside the game since casual play does not require it.<br>
<br>
Naari Evenstar - Mage of the 42nd level of training and proud member of the Wolves of Antonica.<br>
<br>
Lorria Evenstar - Cleric of 41 levels also of the Wolves of Antonica <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khub>khub</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/02 4:13:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3323.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Damn dirty Yantis</span><hr size=1>  Unfortunately I think that the OOC world already affects the way people play this game, for example some people spend all there free time here, some people have 2 boxes and 2 accounts and can play 2 chars at the same time. These abilities are limited by real life, can you afford 2 accs, 2 comps, and not to work so that you can play all the time.<br>
<br>
 I am not saying that I would buy anything from these people for RL Â£, nor am I condoning the methods used to &quot;farm&quot; the items or whatever that are available to purchase. <br>
<br>
 I would say I am new to any kind of RPing and not sure of the pen and paper side of things, I realise that some people reading this forum may have been doing this for years, so I put a question to these people: If I had to work away from home in RL for a week I wouldn't get my fix of EQ and wouldn't have made my usual 400 plat in that week ( don't laugh that is my average income not being much of a trader).<br>
  <br>
 Now with the money I make from my extra hours or whatever I buy the plat to purchase a bridle.<br>
<br>
 If I were to return to my friends in game on horseback they would ask firstly where I had been, and secondly where I got the horse ( just an example I don't have a horse or work away from home much at all). If I were to reply that I had taken a job mucking out stables on the moon in return for an old nag that was headed for the knackers yard and had the Rp tale of what happened is that not as valid a way of role playing as any other.<br>
<br>
 It ain't going happen mind you this is a purely hypothetical conundrum. Just wanted an opinion or 2.<br>
<br>
Anyway just wondered how this sort of thing stands. If it is a ridiculous idea say so.<br>
<br>
Yours<br>
Khub 47th Season warrior.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caillougna>Caillou GNA</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pebble with a bow</span><br>  Posts: 955<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/02 4:32:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3323.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Damn dirty Yantis</span><hr size=1> I'd applaud you for coming up with an RP story (which you could have done even from earning it in game), but if I knew you got it with real money, I would sigh and my opinion of you would drop some.  I wouldn't use it as the only thing for which to turn my back on you, I jsut wouldn't have as high of an opinion of you.  Now, if you did it all the time or let that one thing let you be drawn to the dark side.... you see.. it is a slippery slope, if you take the easy route once (some of us can afford more in RL than we can in-game), then you'll see it is easy to justify again.  Not everyone does, but... it is jsut to easy to succumb to such.  <br>
<br>
(btw, I actually do know someone who bought something for real money on this server, and I disagree with that person for doing so, but I don't shun the person for it) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=twotribes>Twotribes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Troll</span><br>  Posts: 641<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/02 6:59:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3323.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Damn dirty Yantis</span><hr size=1> Just as how I choose to play is my buisness, how I choose to spend my real life money is mine. If I want to buy a pile of platinum that is my buisness.<br>
<br>
This is like the twinking threads, whines about how it is cheating to allow others to have stuff are just that whines. Let me see if I have this right. If I get Joe schmuck to give me 20000 PP for what ever reason that is ok, but if I buy 20000 PP that is bad.<br>
<br>
If you dont agree with buying items and money, Dont. If you catch someone hacking the game, report them.  So where are all these mythical farmers at? Who has been denied the opportunity to hunt somewhere exactly?<br>
<br>
When someone posts a provable condition where others have been denied the ability to hunt somewhere cause Joe Farmer was there to raise cash to sell for real life cash, maybe I will worry about it. Till then I havent been inconvienced by any farmers except the times I wanted to hunt Hill Giants to get PP myself. And I doubt any of them were farmers of PP for sale to the highest bidder, they were just people like me trying to raise some cash.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimjakkghostripper>Grimjakk Ghostripper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/02 10:32:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3323.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Damn dirty Yantis</span><hr size=1> On this server?  Probably not yet.  Happens all the time on others tho'.  Go check out Tallon some time.<br>
