Eventually tho', the folks who cared more about being &quot;uber&quot; and &quot;winning&quot; started to crossteam.  They had all sorts of rationalizations, but what it came down to was that it was easier to ignore the rules of the community and group/guild with the enemy than it was to fight.  <br>
